Run CHUNK 4 to plot some variables as scatterplots.

Plot vs dollars.Going to log-transform the dollars for scale and remove zero dollars.

#CHUNK 4
library(ggplot2)
library(gridExtra)
p1 <- ggplot(data = meps.sub[meps.sub$TOTEXP14!=0,], aes(x = AGE14X, y = log(TOTEXP14) )) +
       geom_point(color = 1,alpha = 0.1) 
p2 <- ggplot(data = meps.sub[meps.sub$TOTMCD14!=0,], aes(x = AGE14X, y = log(TOTMCD14) )) +
       geom_point(color = 2,alpha = 0.1) 
p3 <- ggplot(data = meps.sub[meps.sub$TOTMCR14!=0,], aes(x = AGE14X, y = log(TOTMCR14) )) +
       geom_point(color = 3,alpha = 0.1) 
p4 <- ggplot(data = meps.sub[meps.sub$TOTOFD14!=0,], aes(x = AGE14X, y = log(TOTOFD14) )) +
       geom_point(color = 4,alpha = 0.1) #+ ylim(2,14)
grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3,p4,ncol=2)

Run CHUNK 6 to calculate a variety of statistics. Ill use age as the numeric variable.
#CHUNK 6
stats.central <- data.frame(mean = mean(meps.sub$AGE14X),
                            median = median(meps.sub$AGE14X),
                            percentile5 = quantile(meps.sub$AGE14X, 0.05),
